Lead target covered with the uranium blanket
was irradiated by the 1.6-GeV deuteron beam from the
Nuclotron accelerator. Neutrons generated in the
sub-critical uranium blanket are used to activate the
radioactive samples outside the blanket. On the top
of the second section of the blanket, natU, 232Th,
a set of other radioactive samples like 129I, 238Pu,
natMo, 56Fe, natNi, 55Mn, natTi, natCo were placed.
The neutron flux at the position of activation samples
was simulated using the MCNPX code.
flux comes out to be 2.17x10**7 n/cm2/s for the 55Mn,
Calculated by MCNPX neutron fluence dependence from En
is given of fig.2 of J,ARI,70,(7),1254,2012 in energy
range from 7.E-3 eV to 1.5E+3 MeV, peak about 1.5 MeV.
EN-MIN - EN-MAX = 1 eV - 10 MeV were used in Subents
